@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy — TechWayFit Pulse";
}

<main class="py-5">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px;">
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-5">
            <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="text-muted">Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">1. Information We Collect</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">
                        TechWayFit Pulse collects minimal information necessary to provide workshop facilitation services. This includes:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-muted">
                        <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Only your email address and name. We use Email OTP (One-Time Password) for authentication and do not store passwords or authentication credentials</li>
                        <li><strong>Participant Information:</strong> Limited to participant name (optional) and custom data fields configured by the facilitator for specific workshops</li>
                        <li><strong>Workshop Data:</strong> Session titles, activities, and participant responses (which may be anonymous)</li>
                        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Basic log data for service operation and debugging purposes</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">We use collected information to:</p>
                    <ul class="text-muted">
                        <li>Authenticate you via secure email-based one-time passwords (no password storage)</li>
                        <li>Provide and maintain the Pulse workshop platform</li>
                        <li>Enable real-time collaboration and data collection during workshops</li>
                        <li>Generate reports and analytics for facilitators</li>
                        <li>Improve and optimize our services</li>
                        <li>Communicate with you about your account and our services</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">
                        Your data is stored securely using industry-standard encryption. Workshop sessions expire after 6 hours by default,
                        and all associated participant data is automatically deleted unless explicitly saved by the facilitator.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                        We only store your name and email address for account purposes. We do not store passwords—authentication
                        is handled through secure one-time passwords (OTP) sent to your email.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">4. AI Context and Processing</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                        When you use AI-powered features to generate session content or get facilitation assistance, any context
                        or prompts you share are sent to the AI service provider for processing. <strong>We do not persist or store
                        this AI context data.</strong> The AI-generated responses are provided to you in real-time and are not
                        saved to our servers beyond the session scope.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">5. Anonymous Participation</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">
                        Participants can choose to respond anonymously during workshop activities. When anonymous mode is enabled,
                        we do not collect or store personally identifiable information linked to those responses. Even when participants
                        provide their name, we only collect the name and specific data fields that the facilitator has configured
                        for the workshop (such as department, role, or other custom fields).
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">6. Data Sharing</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">
                        We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. Workshop data is only accessible
                        to the facilitator who created the session and participants with the session code.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">You have the right to:</p>
                    <ul class="text-muted">
                        <li>Access your personal data (name and email address)</li>
                        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                        <li>Request deletion of your account and associated workshop data</li>
                        <li>Export your workshop data and participant responses</li>
                        <li>Opt-out of non-essential communications</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                        <strong>Note:</strong> We maintain minimal data—only your name and email. Sessions automatically expire
                        after 6 hours unless saved, and AI context is never persisted.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-5">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">8. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">
                        We use essential cookies to maintain your session and preferences. We do not use third-party tracking cookies
                        or analytics beyond what is necessary for the platform to function.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted">
                        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting
                        the new policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">10. Contact Us</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
                        <a href="/home/support" class="text-decoration-none fw-medium">Support Center</a>
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Back to Home -->
        <div class="text-center mt-4">
            <a href="/" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2">
                <i class="fas fa-home"></i>
                <span>Back to Home</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>
